error cannot lock the xauthority file when attempting to connect using vnc or starting x windows stanford answers stanford university stanford answers error cannot lock the xauthority file when attempting to connect using vnc or starting x windows categories accounts and ids administrative applications anti virus and security computer operating systems connecting to the network desktop hardware and support email and calendar help desk restricted information on it services software at stanford stanford hospital and clinics telephones and cable tv unix systems and software web services user login login with your sunet id home error cannot lock the xauthority file when attempting to connect using vnc or starting x windows search this site the most common cause of this error message is that insufficient space exists in a user's home directory to accommodate the x windows startup procedure or the vnc log file enough space must be freed before x windows or vnc will run normally it is also possible though less common for the xauthority file to remain locked by a previous x windows session in this case it is usually safe to re authenticate and then remove the xauthority file in order to clear the lock kinit aklog rm f xauthority unix systems software stanford university 450 serra mall stanford california 94305 650 723 2300 terms of use copyright complaints
